# .trivyignore — suppressed Trivy CVE findings
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  reason: <justification>; revisit: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Rules:
#   - Every entry MUST include a brief justification and an expiry / revisit date.
#   - Remove entries once the CVE is fixed upstream or the revisit date has passed
#     and the risk has been re-evaluated.
#   - Only suppress findings that are genuinely not exploitable in this threat model
#     (e.g. the vulnerable code path is not reachable) or that have a tracked
#     upstream fix expected before the expiry date.
#
# No suppressions are currently active. Add them here as needed.
